olive oil
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 carrot
½ tin cannellini beans
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet tomato paste
⅓ cup water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 tomato
1 bag herbs
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat!
• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop mild chorizo. Grate the carrot. Drain and rinse cannellini beans
(see ingredients).
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook chorizo, tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes.
• Add the brown sugar, tomato paste and Tex-Mex spice blend and cook
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add cannellini beans and carrot and cook until softened and starting to
break down, 3-4 minutes.
• Add the water and baby spinach leaves and cook until wilted, 1 minute.

• Arrange mini flour tortillas over a lined oven tray.
• Divide chorizo filling between tortillas, spooning it onto one half of each
tortilla, then top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Fold empty half of each tortilla over to enclose filling and press down gently
with a spatula. Brush (or spray) tortillas with a drizzle of olive oil. Season
with salt and pepper.
• Bake quesadillas until cheese has melted and tortillas are golden,
8-12 minutes. Spoon any overflowing filling back into quesadillas.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, finely chop tomato and herbs.
• In a small bowl, combine tomato, herbs and a light drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide cheesy chorizo and cannellini bean quesadillas between plates.
• Serve with herby tomato salsa. Enjoy!